My personal list of about:config tweaks for maximum performance, usablitity, privacy, with little to no breakage.
a value of "true" means the setting will be enabled, a value of "false" means the setting will be disabled
(I'll specify in parentheses if the parameter requires additional knowledge)
If "hidden preference" is noted, you must type in the parameter and select "Boolean" and click the "+" indicator to create the parameter.
The extension "uBlock Origin" will be mentioned as it changes some parameters in its native settings; I HIGHLY recommend installing it as your only content blocker.
(listed in order of the "Show All" button)

accesibility.force_enabled; false (turns off accessiblity services; could break some sites that launch external tools)
app.normandy.enabled; false
app.normandy.first_run; false
app.shield.optoutstudies.enabled; false
beacon.enabled; false
browser.backspace_action; 2 (depends on the user; A value of 2 prevents Firefox from going back a page if you press the backspace bar without a form entry)
browser.display.focus_ring_width; 0
browser.download.animateNotifications; false
browser.download.autohideButton; false
browser.formfill.enable; false (depends on the user; if using Firefox's native password manager "Lockwise," then ignore, but using a password manager like Bitwarden renders autofill useless)
browser.overlink-delay; 0
browser.ping-centre.telemetry; false
browser.search.separatePrivateDefault; true
browser.search.separatePrivateDefault.ui.enabled; true
browser.send_pings.require_same_host; true
browser.shell.checkDefaultBrowser; false
browser.startup.blankWindow; false
browser.tabs.closeWindowWithLastTab; false (if you have only one tab open and click then exit button on the tab rectangle, Firefox won't close)
browser.tabs.crashReporting.sendReport; false
browser.tabs.loadBookmarksInTabs; true (loads bookmarks in a new tab and therefore prevents tab hijacking/losing sensitive work)
browser.urlbar.speculativeConnect.enabled; false
browser.urlbar.trimURLs; false (shows the http/https header always)
datareporting.healthreport.uploadEnabled; false
datareporting.policy.dataSubmissionEnabled; false
device.sensors.enabled; false
dom.enable_resource_timing; false (prevents websites from accessing javascript resource timing)
dom.ipc.plugins.reportCrashURL; false
dom.serviceWorkers.enabled; false (will cause site breakage, I personally have no use for them, however, service workers are used extensively for web notifications and other functionality, for more info, see https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Service_Worker_API)
dom.vibrator.enabled; false
dom.webnotifications.enabled; false (depends on user; setting to false will block all web notifications and save some CPU)
extensions.getAddons.showPane; false (hidden preference, removes "recommended" extensions pane on about:addons)
extensions.pocket.enabled; false (pocket is equivalent to "MSN" in Microsoft Edge; this uses extra CPU)
extensions.webextensions.restrictedDomains; ""
gfx.downloadable_fonts.fallback_delay; 0
gfx.downloadable_fonts.fallback_delay; 0
gfx.font_loader.delay; 0
gfx.webrender.all; true (may expreience some bugs, but enables Mozilla's "webrender," which increases peformance significantly)
media.peerconnection.ice.default_address_only; true (uBlock Origin setting: "Prevent WebRTC from leaking local IP addresses")
media.peerconnection.ice.no_host; true (uBlock Origin setting: "Prevent WebRTC from leaking local IP addresses")
media.peerconnection.ice.proxy_only_if_behind_proxy; true (uBlock Origin setting: "Prevent WebRTC from leaking local IP addresses")
media.peerconnection.identity.timeout; 1
media.videocontrols.picture-in-picture.allow-multiple; true
media.video_stats.enabled; false
network.IDN_show_punycode; true (for phishing attacks; see https://www.ghacks.net/2017/04/17/punycode-phishing-attack-fools-even-die-hard-internet-veterans/)
network.predictor.enabled; false (uBlock Origin setting: "Disable pre-fetching (to prevent any connection for blocked network requests)")
network.prefetch-next; false (uBlock Origin setting: "Disable pre-fetching (to prevent any connection for blocked network requests)")
privacy.resistFingerprinting.block_mozAddonManager; true (hidden preference to allow extensions to run on Mozilla websites)
network.security.esni.enabled; true (enables ESNI (Encrypted Server Name Indication) if using certain DNS over HTTPS (DoH) servers, see https://www.cloudflare.com/learning/ssl/what-is-encrypted-sni/)
reader.parse-on-load.enabled; false (depends on user; setting this to false disables "reader mode")
security.dialog_enable_delay; 0
security.family_safety.mode; 0
security.notification_enable_delay; 0
toolkit.coverage.opt-out; true
toolkit.legacyUserProfileCustomizations.stylesheets; true (must enable if you want to use CSS to customize Firefox, see https://www.userchrome.org/)
toolkit.telemetry.archive.enabled; false
toolkit.telemetry.bhrPing.enabled; false
toolkit.coverage.endpoint.base; " "
toolkit.telemetry.coverage.opt-out; true (hidden preference)
toolkit.telemetry.newProfilePing.enabled; false
toolkit.telemetry.server; " "
toolkit.telemetry.shutdownPingSender.enabled; false
toolkit.telemetry.unified; false
toolkit.telemetry.updatePing.enabled; false
